    "claim": "`routerCall` computes fees and downstream spend from `_params.srcInputAmount`, but never measures how many tokens were really received by `safeTransferFrom`. For fee-on-transfer, rebasing, or otherwise balance-deflating tokens, the proxy can approve and spend more than it actually got from the caller.",
    "impact": "If the proxy already holds reserves of the same token, such as accrued fees or stranded balances, an attacker can bridge or pull a larger amount than they contributed and consume the shortfall from those reserves. This turns any proxy-held balance of a deflationary token into a subsidy that can be drained.",
    "paths": [
      "The proxy already holds some balance of a deflationary token.",
      "An attacker calls `routerCall` with that token as `srcInputToken`.",
      "`safeTransferFrom` delivers less than `_params.srcInputAmount`, but fees and `_amountIn` are still computed from the larger nominal amount.",
      "The gateway spends `_amountIn`, and the missing portion is silently funded out of the proxy's pre-existing balance."
    ]
  },
